-- Sotheby’s Hong Kong Sales See Fewer China Buyers, Ming Pao Says
-- B y   H w e e   A n n   T a n
-- 2012-05-17T23:58:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-17/sotheby-s-hong-kong-sales-see-fewer-china-buyers-ming-pao-says.html
Sotheby’s Hong Kong spring auction
sales fell 30 percent to HK$2.46 billion ($317 million) from a
year earlier because there were fewer mainland Chinese buyers,
Ming Pao Daily reported today, citing  Kevin Ching , chief
executive officer of Sotheby’s Asia.  About half of the Chinese buyers were speculators,
according to the Chinese-language newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hwee Ann Tan at 
 hatan@bloomberg.net  